{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Vn1eFbYijMXLDAR9A3m9Zy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01EA1Q3MoVkzkY5TLe9tq1Hg","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Draft LaTeX setup and file layout sections","subagent_type":"researcher","team_name":"category-theory-book-plan","name":"latex-specialist","prompt":"You are a LaTeX and mathematical typography specialist on an editorial team producing a comprehensive plan for a graduate-level category theory book. Your job is to draft TWO sections of the plan in detail. Write your output as Markdown — thorough, specific, and production-ready. Do NOT write to disk; just produce the text.\n\n---\n\n## SECTION 1: LaTeX Setup\n\nProduce a detailed, opinionated recommendation covering:\n\n### Document Class\n- Recommend `memoir` as the primary class (explain why over `book`: built-in chapter styles, better control over headers/footers, epigraph support, etc.)\n- Key class options: `[12pt, a4paper, twoside, openright]` or similar, with explanation\n- Alternatively discuss `scrbook` (KOMA-Script) as a secondary option and when to prefer it\n\n### Essential Packages (with purpose of each)\nList and explain at minimum:\n- `tikz-cd` (commutative diagrams — the cornerstone)\n- `tikz` with libraries: `arrows.meta`, `decorations.pathmorphing`, `calc`\n- `amsthm` (theorem environments)\n- `amsmath`, `mathtools` (math typesetting; explain `\\coloneqq`, `\\mathrel`, etc.)\n- `amssymb`, `mathrsfs` (for script letters like `\\mathscr{C}`)\n- `hyperref` (links, PDF metadata)\n- `cleveref` (smart cross-references — must load AFTER hyperref)\n- `enumitem` (custom list styles for exercises)\n- `microtype` (microtypography, protrusion, expansion)\n- `thmtools` (for `\\listoftheorems`)\n- `todonotes` (author annotations during drafting)\n- `biblatex` with `biber` backend\n- `xcolor` (for diagram colors, author notes)\n- `booktabs` (for any tables)\n- `inputenc`/`fontenc` or `unicode-math` + `fontspec` (if XeLaTeX/LuaLaTeX)\n- `makeidx` or `imakeidx` (index generation)\n- Any other packages you deem essential\n\n### Theorem/Definition/Remark/Example Environments\nUsing `amsthm` and `thmtools`, specify:\n- Which `\\theoremstyle` for each type (plain, definition, remark)\n- Which environments to define: Theorem, Proposition, Lemma, Corollary, Definition, Example, Remark, Warning, Notation, Construction, Exercise\n- Numbering scheme (by section, by chapter — recommend and justify)\n- Use of `thmtools`' `\\listoftheorems` and `shaded` option\n- Sample amsthm code block showing how to define these\n\n### BibLaTeX Configuration\n- Backend: biber\n- Style: alphabetic (e.g., [ML98] for Mac Lane 1998) — justify this choice\n- Key options: `giveninits=true`, `maxbibnames=99`, `doi=false`, `isbn=false`, `url=false` (explain each)\n- Citation commands: `\\cite`, `\\textcite`, `\\parencite` — when to use each\n- How to handle classic references (Eilenberg–Mac Lane 1945, etc.)\n\n### Custom Macros (macros.tex)\nList essential category theory macros to define:\n- `\\cat{C}` for categories (using `\\mathbf` or `\\mathcal`)\n- `\\func{F}{C}{D}` for functors\n- `\\Hom`, `\\Ob`, `\\Mor`\n- `\\op` for opposite category\n- `\\iso` for isomorphism arrow\n- `\\eqv` for equivalence\n- Composition: `\\circ` conventions, `\\then` for diagrammatic order\n- Natural transformation arrow: `\\Rightarrow`, `\\nat`\n- `\\colim`, `\\lim`\n- `\\Set`, `\\Grp`, `\\Top`, `\\Ab`, `\\Cat`, `\\Pos` as named categories\n- 2-cell / double-category notation if relevant\n\n---\n\n## SECTION 6: File/Directory Layout\n\nProduce a complete, annotated directory tree for the LaTeX project, covering:\n\n- `main.tex` — the root file (what it contains: `\\documentclass`, `\\input{preamble}`, `\\include` for each chapter, etc.)\n- `preamble.tex` — all `\\usepackage` and global settings\n- `macros.tex` — all `\\newcommand` definitions (sourced from preamble)\n- `chapters/` subdirectory:\n  - `00-frontmatter.tex` (title page, dedication, preface)\n  - `01-categories.tex`\n  - `02-functors.tex`\n  - `03-natural-transformations.tex`\n  - `04-limits-and-colimits.tex`\n  - `05-adjoints.tex`\n  - `06-monads.tex`\n  - `07-kan-extensions.tex`\n  - `08-enriched-categories.tex` (optional advanced chapter)\n  - `appendix-A-set-theory.tex`\n  - `appendix-B-logic.tex`\n- `figures/` subdirectory — conventions for naming and organizing tikz-cd figures vs. standalone `.tex` figure files\n- `bibliography.bib` — BibTeX database\n- `index-entries.tex` or inline `\\index{}` conventions\n- `Makefile` or `latexmkrc` — build automation (explain latexmk workflow with biber)\n- `.gitignore` for LaTeX projects\n\nShow the tree as a proper ASCII/Markdown tree, then annotate each file/directory with its purpose and key contents.\n\nAlso describe the build workflow: `latexmk -pdf -pvc main.tex`, the biber run, index generation with `makeindex` or `xindy`.\n\n---\n\nFormat your output as clean Markdown with level-2 (`##`) headers for Section 1 and Section 6, and level-3 (`###`) subheaders within each. Be concrete and specific — include actual LaTeX code blocks where helpful. This will go directly into a production plan document.","run_in_background":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":202,"cache_read_input_tokens":24521,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":202},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fa7cc145-2f78-404b-95d8-111f11645337","uuid":"021c231f-81d4-430e-9a64-e5148452362f"}
